785. scibitur=scz'etur. In the classieal period the true future in -bo was only used with verbs of the first and second cmrjugation, while the subjunctive form was used instead of the future in those of the third and fourth, e.g. capiam, sciam. But this rule was not observed at Plautus’ time, so we have the fut. of the 4th conjugation in -bo in his plays. We even find a third conjugation future in -bo, viz. reddffbo in Men. 5. 7. 49. but this is due to the form of the future of the simple verb, dabo.
